ex you should be able to override this even if it isn't set ConditionalOnMissingBean possibly with the `@Primary` annotation.
```
  @Bean CollectorSampler traceIdSampler(@Value("${zipkin.collector.sample-rate:1.0}") float rate) {
    return CollectorSampler.create(rate);
  }
```

we can also change that bean to conditionalOnMissingBean

AFAIU this has been implemented, sampling can be done [declaratively](https://github.com/openzipkin/brave/tree/master/brave#declarative-sampling) or [custom](https://github.com/openzipkin/brave/tree/master/brave#custom-sampling) which is what this issue refers to:

```
SamplerFunction<Request> requestBased = (request) -> {
  if (request.url().startsWith("/experimental")) {
    return true;
  } else if (request.url().startsWith("/static")) {
    return false;
  }
  return null;
};
```
